handNote.desc:
The handwriting retains old paleographic features: 
                            ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line (e.g., twice on ), or with a ver small linking line; 
                            the upper part of some letters, e.g. ቆ, ቶ, የ, ደ, ጸ, has a triangular shape; 
                            the left stroke of some letters, e.g. ሰ, በ, ዘ, is sometimes slanted; 
                            ማ has the stroke to the left of the right loop, which has an unusual shape; 
                            numerals are written without dashes; 
                            ፪ has angular and not separated loops.
